{
  "texts": [
    "However, this proposal faces a significant challenge.",
    "On the argument pressed in a series of papers by Ken Adams and Frank Aizawa (see, e.g., their 2001, 2010, 2019; see also Aizawa, 2015 Aizawa,, 2017)), arguments from offloading to HEC fall foul of the 'coupling-constitution fallacy': the illegitimate inference from two things being causally integrated to their constituting a single process or phenomenon.",
    "This argument has been influential.",
    "However, it is far from clear that coupling is always incompatible with constitution.",
    "Indeed, a standard understanding of a 'mechanism' in the philosophy of science literature characterises it as a reliably integrated group of causally integrated elements that together constitute a phenomenon of interest (see, e.g., Craver, 2007)."
  ]
}